## Proposed Changes

### Component: `agent-api/` (New Project)

---

#### [NEW] `package.json`
Dependencies:
- `express`, `dotenv`, `cors`, `multer` (for file upload)
- `@x402/express`, `@x402/stellar`, `@x402/core` (x402 payment middleware)
- `groq-sdk` (LLM + STT via Groq Whisper)
- `@deepgram/sdk` (STT Nova-3, TTS Aura)
- `@fal-ai/client` (Image Generation)
- `pinata` (IPFS Storage)
- `@huggingface/inference` (HuggingFace models)
- `tsx`, `typescript` (devDependencies)

---

#### [NEW] `.env.example`
```env
# Stellar
STELLAR_ADDRESS=GB3XY...
FACILITATOR_URL=https://stellar-bazar.onrender.com

# Server
PORT=4030
SERVICE_URL=http://localhost:4030

# Provider Keys
GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_...
DEEPGRAM_API_KEY=...
FAL_KEY=...
PINATA_JWT=...
PINATA_GATEWAY=...
HF_ACCESS_TOKEN=hf_...

# Compute (optional - requires Docker)
PISTON_URL=http://localhost:2000
```

---

#### [NEW] `src/utils/pricing.ts`
Defines the **dynamic pricing map** for each route.

| Route | Model/Service | Price (USDC) | How you profit |
|---|---|---|---|
| `POST /v1/chat` (model: **auto**) | Groq `llama-3.1-8b-instant` (router picks) | `$0.02` | Groq is almost free. High margin. |
| `POST /v1/chat` (model: **llama-3.3-70b**) | Groq `llama-3.3-70b-versatile` | `$0.05` | Still cheap on Groq. |
| `POST /v1/chat` (model: **llama-4-scout**) | Groq `llama-4-scout-17b-16e-instruct` | `$0.03` | New fast model. |
| `POST /v1/stt` | Deepgram `nova-3` | `$0.05` | Per minute (fractions of a cent). |
| `POST /v1/tts` | Deepgram `aura-2-en-us` | `$0.02` | Per character (fractions of a cent). |
| `POST /v1/image` (model: **flux-schnell**) | `fal-ai/flux/schnell` | `$0.05` | Fast & cheap on fal.ai. |
| `POST /v1/image` (model: **flux-pro**) | `fal-ai/flux-pro` | `$0.15` | Higher quality, higher price. |
| `POST /v1/storage` | Pinata IPFS | `$0.01` | Pinata free tier (1GB). |
| `POST /v1/compute` | Piston (self-hosted) | `$0.10` | You run it. 100% margin. |
| `POST /v1/hf/:model_id` | HuggingFace Serverless | `$0.03` | HF free tier for serverless. |

---

#### [NEW] `src/router.ts` — Intelligent LLM Router
When the agent passes `model: "auto"`, the router analyzes the prompt and picks the best model:

**Routing Logic (Cheap Classification Call):**
1. Fire a sub-100ms call to `llama-3.1-8b-instant` on Groq with a system prompt like: *"You are a routing agent. Classify this prompt as one of: SIMPLE, MEDIUM, COMPLEX. Reply only with the classification word."*
2. Based on the result:
   - `SIMPLE` → Route to `llama-3.1-8b-instant` (fastest, cheapest)
   - `MEDIUM` → Route to `llama-4-scout-17b-16e-instruct` (balanced)
   - `COMPLEX` → Route to `llama-3.3-70b-versatile` (smartest)

---

#### [NEW] `src/server.ts` — Main x402 Express Server
- Sets up `paymentMiddleware` for all 7 routes at once.
- Uses the pricing map to dynamically set each route's price.
- On startup, calls `registerAllInBazaar()` to auto-register every endpoint.

---

#### [NEW] `src/routes/llm.ts`
- Reads `req.body.model` and `req.body.messages`.
- If `model === "auto"`, calls `router.ts` classify function, then routes to the chosen Groq model.
- If a specific model is passed (e.g., `"llama-3.3-70b-versatile"`), routes directly.
- Returns standard OpenAI-format JSON: `{ choices: [{ message: { content: "..." } }] }`.

---

#### [NEW] `src/routes/stt.ts`
- Accepts `multipart/form-data` with an `audio` file.
- Sends audio buffer to Deepgram `nova-3` model via the `@deepgram/sdk`.
- Returns: `{ transcript: "...", confidence: 0.99 }`.

---

#### [NEW] `src/routes/tts.ts`
- Accepts `{ text: "...", voice: "aura-2-en-us" }` (voice is optional).
- Calls Deepgram Aura TTS API.
- Returns an audio buffer (MP3) as `Content-Type: audio/mpeg`.

---

#### [NEW] `src/routes/image.ts`
- Accepts `{ prompt: "...", model: "flux-schnell" | "flux-pro" }`.
- If `model` is not provided, defaults to `flux-schnell`.
- Calls fal.ai `@fal-ai/client` with the given prompt.
- Returns: `{ url: "https://fal.ai/files/...", width: 1024, height: 1024 }`.

---

#### [NEW] `src/routes/storage.ts`
- Accepts `multipart/form-data` with a `file`.
- Uploads to Pinata IPFS using the modern `pinata` SDK.
- Returns: `{ ipfs_hash: "QmXYZ...", gateway_url: "https://gateway.pinata.cloud/ipfs/QmXYZ..." }`.

---

#### [NEW] `src/routes/compute.ts`
- Accepts `{ language: "python", code: "print('hello')" }`.
- Forwards to self-hosted Piston API at `PISTON_URL`.
- Returns: `{ stdout: "hello\n", stderr: "", exit_code: 0 }`.
- If `PISTON_URL` is not set, returns a `503 Service Unavailable` with a helpful message.

---

#### [NEW] `src/routes/hf.ts`
- Dynamic route: `POST /v1/hf/:model_id`.
- Accepts `{ inputs: "...", parameters: {} }`.
- Calls the HuggingFace Serverless Inference API using `@huggingface/inference`.
- Uses generic `hf.request()` so any model is supported.
- Returns the raw HuggingFace API response.

---

#### [NEW] `src/utils/bazaar.ts`
- `registerAllInBazaar()` — On startup, sends `POST /register-service` to the Bazaar for each of the 7 endpoints, including detailed `input_schema`, `output_schema`, and `output_example` so agents can discover and use them autonomously.

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
After building, we will run the following `curl.exe` tests to verify each route:

1. `curl.exe -i http://localhost:4030/v1/chat` → Should return `402 Payment Required`
2. `curl.exe -i http://localhost:4030/v1/image` → Should return `402 Payment Required`
3. `curl.exe -i http://localhost:4030/v1/storage` → Should return `402 Payment Required`
4. Check Bazaar: `curl.exe https://stellar-bazar.onrender.com/discovery/resources?q=unified`

### Manual Verification
1. Start server with `npm run dev` inside `agent-api/`.
2. Confirm all 7 services are registered in the Bazaar discovery API.
3. Check that the `402 Payment Required` header contains the correct Stellar address and pricing.
